WRITING.TITLE: Paralyzed former olympian walks wife down the aisle 15 months after spinal cord injury. Story in Comments.

WRITING.TEXT: The man in the photo is Jaime Nieto, a two-time olympic high jumper who was paralyzed from a spinal cord injury that he sustained in April of last year. Doctors were unsure if he would ever walk again, but after 15 months of intense physical therapy and working out on his own, he was able to fulfill his promise of walking his wife down the aisle at their wedding. [Story here](http://www.nbcbayarea.com/news/california/Injured-Olympic-High-Jumper-Jamie-Nieto-Walks-at-Wedding-in-San-Diego-436029563.html).

He is still partially paralyzed from the shoulders down but he is getting stronger everyday. Paralysis isn't so black and white.. it is not an all or nothing type of thing. He still has a long road ahead of him to regain as much of what he lost as he can..
Haha.. as I stated in the original post, I am a friend of the couple in the "it still works!" photo.. but yes, they had their baby boy in August!
